ructs is followed by an analysis of forms interaction, concepts of identity and constructs of culture/interculture, thus shifting the object of analysis from the subjective to the intersubjective levels of construction and interaction. The focus of the book is on the gradual development of interculturally blended third spaces in the mind of the learner as genuinely new bases for construction. This book takes an interdisciplinary approach, drawing on research in cultural psychology, linguistic anthropology, critical theory, language acquisition and second language learning and shows how culture and interculture need to be emphasized as an integral part of second language learning.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aApplied Linguistics.  aIntercultural Competence.  aLanguage and Culture.  aSecond Language Learning.  aThird Space.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015007870 cprintz978161451153340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161451123640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781614511236423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781614511236/original  a978-3-11-02